21/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Minister of Public Order Igli Toska pledged Tuesday (20 April) that his ministry would deepen reforms to bring its structures into line with EU standards. He spoke before parliament's commission on public order and secret services, which met to discuss recommendations made in the recent European Commission report on Albania. Toska insisted there is no place for incriminated persons in his ministry or police structures and that professionalism would be promoted. (ATA - 20/04/04)
